{
  "texts": [
    "Overall, predicting student's academic performance is crucial for societal and individual success, resulting in a more prosperous future for both individuals and communities.",
    "Numerous studies have been conducted to exploit student data to enrich their education, besides proposing answers to many dimensions of educational settings by utilizing state-of-the-art Artificial Intelligence (AI) techniques.",
    "One of the most innovative uses of AI is academic performance prediction, which helps identify students who are more likely to fail or dropout, create student-centered learning pathways to increase learning effectiveness, and optimize instructional design and development Mozer et al (2019); Nabizadeh et al (2020); Taheri et al (2021); Ouyang et al (2023).",
    "Although the use of Artificial Intelligence (AI) in the field of education has grown over the past few years, more development is needed to capture and acquire insights into many aspects of the learning experience.",
    "One of the fields that study learner's data and best represent AI is Educational Data Mining (EDM), which exploits both Machine Learning (ML) and Deep Learning (DL) techniques in educational research."
  ]
}